Unilever Nigeria has released its unaudited report for the period ended 31st March 2020. The Company recorded turnover of N13.3 billion in the period under review. This represents a 46% increase compared to the previous Quarter 4 2019 and a 31% decline compared to N19.2bn recorded for the corresponding period, Q1 2019. The result shows the company also recorded profit after tax of N1.1bn for the period ended 31st March 2020 representing a 27% decline when compared to N1.5billion recorded for the period ended 31st March 2019. The company through its Corporate Affairs Director, Mrs. ‘Soromidayo George said that ‘Unilever Nigeria remains focused on its strategy to deliver sustainable growth and will continue to monitor the business environment and remain dynamic in its response to challenges to operations and the economy, in the light of Covid-19 pandemic’. VANGUARD Unilever Nigeria has released its unaudited report for the quarter ended December 2019. The Company recorded a N9.13 billion revenue in the period under review. The results reflect challenging trading conditions and the Company’s decision in quarter three to prioritize tightening of credit terms and minimize exposures on trade receivables. January 27, 2020 In "News" …restates commitment to achieve competitive growth in 2020 Unilever Nigeria has released its audited financial statements for the year ended 31 December 2019. The Company recorded a Turnover of N60.5 billion in the year under review.  This represents a decline compared to N92.89bn recorded for the corresponding year, 2018. The… March 30, 2020 In "News" Unilever Nigeria Plc results for quarter ending 31st March 2017 shows continued strong growth. The company posted a turnover and Profit after Tax of N22.2billion and N1.6 billion respectively with improvements across board. The growth in turnover has a strong volume component with a 32% growth in turnover from N16.8… April 19, 2017 In "News"